3
00:01:00,280 --> 00:01:03,340
   

4
00:01:03,340 --> 00:01:06,080
   

5
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:08,867
   

6
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:17,780
Let's get out of here. I feel uneasy here.

7
00:01:17,780 --> 00:01:19,940
What happened to your hand?

8
00:01:19,940 --> 00:01:21,680
It's nothing.

9
00:01:23,980 --> 00:01:25,780
Oh, this was a complete waste of time.

10
00:01:25,780 --> 00:01:29,700
You people just lie through your teeth, huh?

11
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:31,740
You think you can walk away without even an apology?

12
00:01:31,740 --> 00:01:33,420
This happened so suddenly.

13
00:01:33,420 --> 00:01:36,565
Shouldn't we be forgiven for making a mistake?

14
00:01:36,565 --> 00:01:38,500
A mistake?

15
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:40,380
You claim it was a mistake when there's surveillance footage.

16
00:01:40,380 --> 00:01:42,000
But what did you say when there was none?

17
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,540
You called him a murderer.

18
00:01:43,540 --> 00:01:46,280
What gives you the right, huh?

19
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:48,680
Let's just drop it now that it's cleared up.

20
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:51,140
Why are you being so relentless, girl?

21
00:01:51,140 --> 00:01:52,380
Drop it?

22
00:01:52,380 --> 00:01:53,460
Why should I?

23
00:01:53,460 --> 00:01:55,660
My friend was framed for no reason.

24
00:01:55,660 --> 00:01:56,700
He's traumatized!

25
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:58,740
Can you take responsibility for that?

26
00:01:58,740 --> 00:02:02,620
Every single one of you just spews lies without a second thought!

27
00:02:02,620 --> 00:02:04,460
I'm suing you! Just you wait!

28
00:02:04,460 --> 00:02:06,540
Listen to you, running your mouth like that.

29
00:02:06,540 --> 00:02:07,760
The person involved isn't even saying anything.

30
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:09,700
- Why do you have so much to say? 
 - What, you want a fight?

31
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:11,460
Bring it on!

32
00:02:16,580 --> 00:02:18,180
What's going on?

33
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:20,120
You want to throw hands?

34
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:28,760
- I'm sorry. 
 - I'm sorry.

35
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:30,600
I'm sorry.

36
00:02:31,540 --> 00:02:32,660
Stop right there!

37
00:02:32,660 --> 00:02:34,400
Did I say you could leave?

38
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:36,220
- Come back anytime. 
 - Why are you stopping me?

39
00:02:36,220 --> 00:02:38,580
- Make yourselves at home. 
 - Enough.

40
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:41,540
So infuriating.

41
00:02:41,540 --> 00:02:42,740
Let's go.

42
00:02:42,740 --> 00:02:44,640
We need to talk.

43
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:49,140
Does it have to be here?

44
00:02:49,140 --> 00:02:52,960
That cop just reminded me of something important.

45
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:54,460
Why was I chasing him?

46
00:02:54,460 --> 00:02:57,460
Come on, he threw a hotpot at me!

47
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:01,020
So, why did he throw a hotpot at you?

48
00:03:01,020 --> 00:03:02,820
He told me he had a dream last night.

49
00:03:02,820 --> 00:03:06,540
He dreamed about... About that Zhang Tong guy.

50
00:03:06,540 --> 00:03:08,660
Then, I made one extra comment.

51
00:03:08,660 --> 00:03:10,100
I shouldn't have run my mouth.

52
00:03:10,100 --> 00:03:14,740
I said, "Well, it was just you and that woman on the bridge."

53
00:03:14,740 --> 00:03:16,860
"You didn't kill her, did you?"

54
00:03:16,860 --> 00:03:19,300
The moment he heard that, his face went pale.

55
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:21,380
Then, suddenly, he flung the hot pot at me.

56
00:03:21,380 --> 00:03:23,300
Shouldn't I chase him?

57
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:26,200
Then, how did he get those injuries on his face?

58
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:29,020
He...

59
00:03:36,380 --> 00:03:38,140
This is it.

60
00:03:38,140 --> 00:03:40,320
I chased Ma Chao all the way, tripped,

61
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,700
and my hands were covered in blood.

62
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:42,700
Then, I pinned him down.

63
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:44,860
He was writhing in pain.

64
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:49,160
His face had these blisters, like burns.

65
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:50,320
In this shape.

66
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:51,440
What is that?

67
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:54,020
The character "ri"* missing a stroke? 
  (*"Ri" means "sun" in Chinese) 

68
00:03:54,020 --> 00:03:56,400
Looks like a tongue to me.

69
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,700
- A tongue? 
 - Think about it.

70
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:01,660
The situation with Thirteen-Thousand and Mu Dai is kind of similar.

71
00:04:01,660 --> 00:04:03,180
They said they were the murderers.

72
00:04:03,180 --> 00:04:04,560
So, everyone believed they were.

73
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,980
A few careless words.

74
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:07,960
Killing with speech.

75
00:04:19,780 --> 00:04:21,600
This is the ancient character for "mouth."

76
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:24,060
Ancient script?

77
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,480
The relic of ill omen?

78
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,760
Is the relic of ill omen inside Ma Chao?

79
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:29,320
Now it all makes sense.

80
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:30,900
The relic of ill omen fears our blood.

81
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:33,460
That's why his skin had such a severe reaction on contact.

82
00:04:33,460 --> 00:04:36,680
But if the relic of ill omen is inside Ma Chao,

83
00:04:37,460 --> 00:04:40,100
what about Song Tie and Wu Yu Ping?

84
00:04:40,100 --> 00:04:42,420
And there's no way everyone who accused Thirteen-Thousand

85
00:04:42,420 --> 00:04:45,480
has the relic of ill omen inside them, right?

86
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:00,740
Three o'clock.

87
00:05:00,740 --> 00:05:01,900
Still doing rounds this afternoon?

88
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:04,300
- You go at three. 
 - All right.

89
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:38,600
 If someone is possessed by the relic of ill omen, 

90
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:41,161
 their regenerative abilities far exceed normal humans. 

91
00:05:41,161 --> 00:05:43,781
 There's no way he'd remain unconscious. 

92
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:07,200
Where's my access card?

93
00:06:11,220 --> 00:06:12,980
Are you okay? Do you need help?

94
00:06:12,980 --> 00:06:14,820
 You didn't get burned, did you? 

95
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:27,260
Thanks.

96
00:06:31,380 --> 00:06:32,860
What are you doing here?

97
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:34,160
Don't trust me to handle it?

98
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:37,700
Having backup is always reassuring.

99
00:06:38,660 --> 00:06:41,140
Is the relic of ill omen inside Ma Chao?

100
00:06:41,780 --> 00:06:43,540
Strange.

101
00:06:43,540 --> 00:06:45,100
It's not inside him.

102
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:47,560
But there's no trace of it leaving either.

103
00:06:48,140 --> 00:06:52,060
Yet he was clearly terrified of Thirteen-Thousand's blood.

104
00:06:52,060 --> 00:06:54,000
I'm confused.

105
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,480
We'll figure it out.

106
00:06:58,340 --> 00:07:00,540
That optimistic?

107
00:07:00,540 --> 00:07:01,780
Or else?

108
00:07:01,780 --> 00:07:03,280
It's always like this.

109
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:05,680
From complete obscurity to unraveling the threads.

110
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:08,860
The truth always comes to light.

111
00:07:08,860 --> 00:07:09,940
Here, An An.

112
00:07:09,940 --> 00:07:11,180
Have some more.

113
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:12,620
Look how thin you are.

114
00:07:12,620 --> 00:07:15,580
You need to eat more to grow tall.

115
00:07:15,580 --> 00:07:17,140
Open your mouth.

116
00:07:17,140 --> 00:07:19,260
One more bite. One more.

117
00:07:19,260 --> 00:07:21,900
 Mom, I'm hungry. 

118
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,200
 Are you a bottomless pit? 

119
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:24,940
 You just ate lunch! 

120
00:07:24,940 --> 00:07:27,000
 But I'm still hungry. 

121
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,100
 Look over there. Go stand over there. 

122
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:30,420
 Stand over there. 

123
00:07:30,420 --> 00:07:31,900
 Go! 

124
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:35,100
 What a deadweight. 

125
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:36,980
 Unbelievable. 

126
00:07:38,180 --> 00:07:40,680
Some kids are precious ones.

127
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:44,220
Some are just deadweights.

128
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:46,840
Why?

129
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:49,980
Maybe...

130
00:07:50,940 --> 00:07:53,080
love comes in measures.

131
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:56,800
There's just a fine line between trouble and love.

132
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,640
If someone loves you deeply,

133
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:00,140
no matter how much trouble you cause,

134
00:08:00,140 --> 00:08:02,320
you're still their treasure.

135
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:04,580
If they don't love you enough,

136
00:08:06,180 --> 00:08:08,660
no matter how well-behaved you are,

137
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:10,880
you're just a nuisance.

138
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:14,500
 Get lost! 

139
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,180
 Get out! 

140
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:18,760
 Out! 

141
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:22,500
 Mom! 

142
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:28,720
Here, your favorite fries.

143
00:08:29,660 --> 00:08:31,260
Yes.

144
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,480
Come on.

145
00:08:51,420 --> 00:08:54,420
Have you found your mom?

146
00:08:54,420 --> 00:08:57,620
People told me she's dead.

147
00:08:57,620 --> 00:09:00,200
They said she jumped off a bridge.

148
00:09:03,220 --> 00:09:04,900
After everything that's happened lately,

149
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:08,160
I've come to dread the phrase "they say."

150
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,540
Yes.

151
00:09:11,820 --> 00:09:13,380
Mu Dai...

152
00:09:14,540 --> 00:09:16,140
do you need help?

153
00:09:16,140 --> 00:09:19,540
Having someone else around is nicer.

154
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:21,740
Don't forget.

155
00:09:21,740 --> 00:09:24,920
We still have our wild card, Wan Feng Huo.

156
00:09:26,180 --> 00:09:28,180
I don't remember her name.

157
00:09:28,180 --> 00:09:30,740
She loved wearing red high heels.

158
00:09:30,740 --> 00:09:33,760
Lived in one of those round buildings in the old district.

159
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:36,120
But that place has been abandoned for years.

160
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:37,380
Later, she got sick.

161
00:09:37,380 --> 00:09:39,520
Terminally ill.

162
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:43,620
She blamed the doctor for not curing her and stabbed the doctor.

163
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,200
This makes things easier.

164
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,700
Nantian isn't big.

165
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:54,060
We'll start from the hospital.

166
00:09:54,060 --> 00:09:55,860
It shouldn't be hard.

167
00:09:55,860 --> 00:09:57,460
But Mu Dai...

168
00:09:58,540 --> 00:10:02,480
have you thought about why you're looking for her?

169
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:04,960
Does there need to be a reason?

170
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:06,840
I mean,

171
00:10:07,980 --> 00:10:11,080
are you trying to reclaim lost family ties?

172
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:13,060
Hoping to reunite?

173
00:10:13,060 --> 00:10:14,660
No.

174
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:17,200
I just...

175
00:10:17,862 --> 00:10:22,443
I want to return to where I began and see the place I came from.

176
00:10:22,443 --> 00:10:24,623
And maybe ask her why she hated how much I ate,

177
00:10:24,623 --> 00:10:28,728
how I dirtied my clothes, and how I splashed water out of the tub.

178
00:10:28,728 --> 00:10:33,320
I tried so hard, eating less, keeping myself spotless,

179
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:35,813
and wiping the floor dry after every bath.

180
00:10:35,813 --> 00:10:37,993
But she still threw me away.

181
00:10:39,695 --> 00:10:42,120
Love comes in measures.

182
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:44,060
I know that.

183
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:51,040
But those words still cut deep.

184
00:10:53,673 --> 00:10:56,420
Heaven gives every child a mother.

185
00:10:56,420 --> 00:10:59,640
Why couldn't they come with equal love?

186
00:11:01,498 --> 00:11:03,618
I don't understand.

187
00:11:12,704 --> 00:11:15,244
I won't chop your hands off.

188
00:11:16,420 --> 00:11:18,400
All right, let's go home.

189
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:19,920
Okay.

190
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:22,560
Did you have fun today?

191
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:23,720
Yes.

192
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,680
Want to watch cartoons when we get back?

193
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:27,120
Yes.

194
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:29,120
Let's go home.

195
00:11:30,441 --> 00:11:33,582
Mu Dai. It'll get better.

196
00:12:01,613 --> 00:12:03,894
 The relic of ill omen isn't inside Ma Chao. 

197
00:12:03,894 --> 00:12:06,299
 That actually makes sense. 

198
00:12:06,299 --> 00:12:11,700
If Ma Chao were a host, he'd be pathetically weak compared to the others we've seen.

199
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:13,200
Look at you, so sharp.

200
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,780
With those skinny arms of yours, no way you could take down

201
00:12:14,780 --> 00:12:16,240
someone possessed by the relic of ill omen.

202
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:18,340
I'm lean, not weak.

203
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:21,180
Could it be a fragment of the relic of ill omen?

204
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:22,924
A fragment?

205
00:12:22,924 --> 00:12:24,441
Ever heard of "Journey to the West"?

206
00:12:24,441 --> 00:12:28,120
Sun Wu Kong can pluck a hair and create clones of himself.

207
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:30,600
But they're nowhere near as strong as the original.

208
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:33,740
So, maybe Ma Chao had something like a fragment of the relic of ill omen on him,

209
00:12:33,740 --> 00:12:38,500
which dissipated on contact with your blood?

210
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,540
Hong Sha's theory is interesting.

211
00:12:42,540 --> 00:12:45,481
Then, when was this "fragment" placed on him?

212
00:12:45,481 --> 00:12:46,782
That's the key.

213
00:12:46,782 --> 00:12:50,423
Mu Dai's case seemed premeditated, planned.

214
00:12:50,423 --> 00:12:52,864
But Thirteen-Thousand's was sudden.

215
00:12:52,864 --> 00:12:54,385
No way it was arranged in advance.

216
00:12:54,385 --> 00:12:56,786
So, it had to be done on the spot?

217
00:12:56,786 --> 00:12:58,587
Let's go back and check the surveillance footage.

218
00:12:58,587 --> 00:13:01,134
Might find some clues.

219
00:13:01,134 --> 00:13:05,700
If Hong Sha's theory is correct, should we test  those

220
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:10,040
who accused Thirteen-Thousand and Mu Dai with our blood?

221
00:13:13,340 --> 00:13:14,781
Give me that.

222
00:13:14,781 --> 00:13:16,761
Thanks.

223
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:34,960
I've already told you everything I know.

224
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:36,956
I just have some new questions.

225
00:13:36,956 --> 00:13:39,596
Don't worry. You'll be paid.

226
00:13:41,060 --> 00:13:42,540
All right.

227
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:00,680
Who did this?

228
00:14:01,899 --> 00:14:03,340
Have you seen them before?

229
00:14:03,340 --> 00:14:05,840
I've never met any of these three girls.

230
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:08,020
Think harder.

231
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:10,880
I really don't remember.

232
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:12,840
Last time, you said you had.

233
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,040
Last time?

234
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:17,600
Do you remember when you went to the bridge?

235
00:14:18,537 --> 00:14:20,677
How many girls were there?

236
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:24,620
Do you remember their faces?

237
00:14:30,680 --> 00:14:33,720
I've never met any of these three girls.

238
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:34,920
Think harder.

239
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:38,280
I really don't remember.

240
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:39,960
Just as we thought.

241
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:45,040
After contact with our blood, they all retracted their earlier statements.

242
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:53,960
 Thank you for turning yourself in, cooperating with our investigation, 

243
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:55,880
 and providing such crucial leads. 
   

244
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:57,800
We're aware of the recent situation.

245
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,440
Just sign here and you're free to go.

246
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:00,580
We appreciate your cooperation.

247
00:15:00,580 --> 00:15:03,620
We may contact you again if we have further questions.

248
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:16,880
Perfect.

249
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:20,440
Ma Chao is now under police supervision.

250
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:22,160
Just need to wait for him to wake up.

251
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:26,080
But, well, my master's name has been cleared anyway.

252
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:27,240
Congratulations.

253
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:29,940
Whether Ma Chao wakes up or not doesn't even matter.

254
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:32,920
Now we just wait for Thirteen-Thousand.

255
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:35,660
Hope it's good news.

256
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:39,500
What good news?

257
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:43,720
How did it go?

258
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:45,120
What do you think?

259
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:48,920
The Traffic Management Office refused, saying that regulations forbid showing the footage.

260
00:15:54,660 --> 00:15:56,021
But!

261
00:15:56,021 --> 00:15:57,182
Remember who I am?

262
00:15:57,182 --> 00:16:01,380
I switched tactics and went door-to-door

263
00:16:01,380 --> 00:16:03,788
checking security cameras along the street.

264
00:16:03,788 --> 00:16:04,769
And sure enough.

265
00:16:04,769 --> 00:16:07,780
Persistence pays off.

266
00:16:07,780 --> 00:16:09,380
Hand it over.

267
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:30,320
Pause.

268
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:31,560
See that?

269
00:16:31,560 --> 00:16:33,720
Everyone's watching the show, except her.

270
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,540
She looks like she doesn't care.

271
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:39,000
Doesn't care?

272
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:42,220
If she really didn't care, she wouldn't have gone near it.

273
00:16:42,220 --> 00:16:45,160
She clearly approached, then walked away.

274
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:47,220
Any other angles?

275
00:16:50,680 --> 00:16:52,980
Here. Isn't that her?

276
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,880
Dressed head to toe in red.

277
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:00,780
Creepy.

278
00:17:00,780 --> 00:17:05,160
Yes. Her fashion sense is something else.

279
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:10,580
It's indeed a bit weird.

280
00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:19,680
Do you think the fragment of the relic of ill omen came from the woman in red?

281
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:21,780
That should be my mother.

282
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:32,860
Mu Dai, you haven't seen your mother in over 20 years.

283
00:17:32,860 --> 00:17:36,640
And the footage is too blurry to make out her face.

284
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:38,390
Are you sure?

285
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:40,600
Just a feeling.

286
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:43,700
In my memories, she always wore red high heels.

287
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:45,600
Every single pair was red.

288
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:48,040
And even though I can't see her face clearly,

289
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:52,360
the moment I saw her, I felt something.

290
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:23,640
Is there anything else I need to do?

291
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:27,220
You've already done a great job.

292
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:30,180
So, no.

293
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,780
Stopping so soon?

294
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:38,760
But I haven't had enough fun yet.

295
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:41,800
The game shouldn't always be yours to play alone.

296
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:44,760
Others are waiting for their turn.

297
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:46,753
Others?

298
00:18:46,753 --> 00:18:50,013
People like me?

299
00:18:51,420 --> 00:18:53,840
Will I get to meet them?

300
00:18:56,120 --> 00:18:57,720
Yes.

301
00:18:57,720 --> 00:19:00,060
Because you're not alone.

302
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:03,180
One day,

303
00:19:04,736 --> 00:19:07,296
we'll never be apart again.

304
00:19:30,620 --> 00:19:32,780
Ding Guo Hua...

305
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:37,367
a doctor with a Ph.D. from Changqing Medical University

306
00:19:37,367 --> 00:19:41,167
and the academic leader in dermatology at the county hospital,

307
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:45,720
quit his job to open a bookstore.

308
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:47,460
A bookstore?

309
00:19:48,540 --> 00:19:52,000
A promising doctor like him just opened a bookstore?

310
00:19:53,140 --> 00:19:54,620
There's more.

311
00:19:54,620 --> 00:19:56,900
Keep reading.

312
00:19:56,900 --> 00:19:59,280
He was stabbed by your mother.

313
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:01,620
Shortly after, he resigned.

314
00:20:01,620 --> 00:20:04,760
But he never pressed charges against her.

315
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:07,980
Also, your mother's surname is Xiang.

316
00:20:08,660 --> 00:20:10,440
Xiang Si Lan.

317
00:20:17,021 --> 00:20:19,621
Xiang Si Lan?

318
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:26,940
Would he know where my mother is?

319
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:29,700
There must be some connection

320
00:20:30,280 --> 00:20:32,700
between him and your mother.

321
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:39,320
Don't worry.

