00:21:17,281 --> 00:21:19,692
Feel free to choose.

326
00:21:19,692 --> 00:21:22,192
Excuse me, is Dr. Ding Guo Hua here?

327
00:21:32,760 --> 00:21:34,140
Who are you?

328
00:21:34,140 --> 00:21:35,900
What do you want?

329
00:21:36,580 --> 00:21:38,720
You're Dr. Ding Guo Hua, right?

330
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:40,320
What do you want?

331
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:44,020
We'd like to consult you on some medical matters.

332
00:21:48,417 --> 00:21:50,177
Medical consultation?

333
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,520
This way.

334
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:53,720
Come on.

335
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:56,060
Here.

336
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:04,440
Have a seat.

337
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:12,460
Who needs medical consultation?

338
00:22:12,460 --> 00:22:14,840
I'm here for my mother.

339
00:22:17,080 --> 00:22:18,140
Who?

340
00:22:18,140 --> 00:22:20,820
I'm here for my mother.

341
00:22:21,999 --> 00:22:23,820
- How long has she been ill? 
 - A long time.

342
00:22:23,820 --> 00:22:26,800
Then, have her come in now.

343
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:28,320
You treated her before.

344
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,940
Diagnosed her with squamous cell carcinoma.

345
00:22:29,940 --> 00:22:32,500
Said it was terminal. Incurable.

346
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:36,520
What... What was her name?

347
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:38,300
Xiang Si Lan.

348
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:40,100
You treated her before, didn't you?

349
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:42,420
Do you know where she is?

350
00:22:42,937 --> 00:22:44,517
There!

351
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:52,640
Xiang Si Lan.

352
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:54,545
Squamous cell carcinoma.

353
00:22:54,545 --> 00:22:57,600
From diagnosis to prescription. Nothing wrong.

354
00:22:57,600 --> 00:23:00,580
I cured her! I cured her!

355
00:23:00,580 --> 00:23:01,860
Why are you saying I didn't?

356
00:23:01,860 --> 00:23:02,940
You're slandering me!

357
00:23:02,940 --> 00:23:04,460
What do you want?

358
00:23:04,460 --> 00:23:05,680
What are you doing?

359
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:07,660
Calm down.

360
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:11,320
I can't say.

361
00:23:11,320 --> 00:23:12,900
If I do, I'll make a mistake.

362
00:23:12,900 --> 00:23:14,780
I can't say.

363
00:23:30,140 --> 00:23:31,280
Dad?

364
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:32,900
Dad!

365
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:34,580
I'm his daughter.

366
00:23:34,580 --> 00:23:37,460
Dad, it's me.

367
00:23:44,420 --> 00:23:46,900
Actually...

368
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:49,245
he's always been ill.

369
00:23:49,245 --> 00:23:55,340
But I'm busy with work, so I keep him with me to look after him.

370
00:23:56,100 --> 00:23:58,620
He rarely has episodes now.

371
00:23:58,620 --> 00:24:00,940
Just gets disoriented occasionally.

372
00:24:00,940 --> 00:24:05,140
When he's like that, he insists on treating patients.

373
00:24:05,140 --> 00:24:07,520
People just humor him.

374
00:24:08,040 --> 00:24:10,700
So, when did his condition start?

375
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:14,540
About 20 years ago.

376
00:24:14,540 --> 00:24:18,641
Back then, he began misdiagnosing every patient.

377
00:24:18,641 --> 00:24:21,302
He said whenever he saw medical records,

378
00:24:21,302 --> 00:24:26,520
he felt an uncontrollable urge to lie.

379
00:24:26,520 --> 00:24:29,780
And at the time, he was a renowned doctor.

380
00:24:29,780 --> 00:24:33,285
So, he misdiagnosed many people.

381
00:24:33,285 --> 00:24:35,685
Including your mother,

382
00:24:37,090 --> 00:24:39,070
Xiang Si Lan.

383
00:24:55,480 --> 00:25:00,140
 Well, your condition will only deteriorate. 

384
00:25:00,140 --> 00:25:02,210
 I've done all I can. 

385
00:25:02,900 --> 00:25:05,200
 So, you're saying... 

386
00:25:05,940 --> 00:25:08,260
 it can't be cured? 

387
00:25:08,260 --> 00:25:14,460
 Currently, there aren't any better options for your illness in the medical field. 

388
00:25:34,180 --> 00:25:35,744
 It's fine. 

389
00:25:35,744 --> 00:25:37,324
 It's all right. 

390
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:39,740
 It can't be cured. 

391
00:25:55,700 --> 00:25:57,600
What happened after that?

392
00:25:57,600 --> 00:26:00,840
After you found out, did you just let it continue?

393
00:26:03,060 --> 00:26:07,520
One night, my father suddenly realized what was happening.

394
00:26:07,520 --> 00:26:08,680
He was horrified.

395
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:13,020
He said he'd take all the misdiagnosed records to the hospital director.

396
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:18,400
But the next day, he was like a different person.

397
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:22,300
Cunning and shady.

398
00:26:22,300 --> 00:26:25,060
He even tried to keep lying.

399
00:26:25,780 --> 00:26:29,540
I was too young back then. I couldn't do anything.

400
00:26:29,540 --> 00:26:32,100
Every day, I just watched him

401
00:26:32,100 --> 00:26:35,540
swing back and forth between those two states.

402
00:26:36,360 --> 00:26:39,020
Your mother was the worst case.

403
00:26:39,020 --> 00:26:43,420
Her treatment was delayed until it was too late.

404
00:26:43,420 --> 00:26:47,640
Then one day, my father...

405
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:50,320
 Did you see it? 

406
00:26:50,320 --> 00:26:52,520
 See that? Who is that? 

407
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:53,800
 Look at her face! 

408
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:55,500
 - Careful. 
 - Disgusting. 

409
00:26:55,500 --> 00:26:57,180
 How dare you show your face here? 

410
00:26:57,180 --> 00:26:58,980
 She actually has the nerve to come back. 

411
00:26:58,980 --> 00:27:01,320
 Covered up like that. Too ashamed to show your face? 

412
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:03,120
 You're not leaving until you explain yourself! 

413
00:27:03,120 --> 00:27:06,220
 Tell us the truth! 

414
00:27:06,220 --> 00:27:08,460
 - Explain yourself! 
 - Don't go! 

415
00:27:08,460 --> 00:27:10,640
 - Stop her! 
 - Don't let her go! 

416
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:12,200
 Behave! 

417
00:27:20,420 --> 00:27:21,820
 You want to see it? 

418
00:27:21,820 --> 00:27:23,500
 Then, take a good look. 

419
00:27:23,500 --> 00:27:25,180
 Listen here, you shameless wretch! 

420
00:27:25,180 --> 00:27:27,720
 What did you put in people's food? 

421
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:28,860
 Your blood is disgusting. 

422
00:27:28,860 --> 00:27:32,000
 Exactly! You being dirty is one thing. 

423
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:35,460
 But dragging everyone else down with you? That's just evil! 

424
00:27:35,460 --> 00:27:37,360
 You're despicable! 

425
00:27:37,360 --> 00:27:39,860
 You're lying! You're all lying! 

426
00:27:39,860 --> 00:27:41,080
 - Did you see it? 
 - I saw it! 

427
00:27:41,080 --> 00:27:44,120
 - Did any of you see it? 
 - You lifted every lid on those pots. 

428
00:27:44,120 --> 00:27:45,240
 What else could you do? 

429
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:46,920
 Spat in it or dripped your blood, right? 

430
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:48,680
 - That's right! 
 - Absolutely! 

431
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:51,080
 Then, sue me! Have the police arrest me! 

432
00:27:51,080 --> 00:27:52,600
 - We're calling the police! 
 - We're calling them! 

433
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:55,640
 You claim I spat and dripped my blood. 

434
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:57,760
 Now I'll... 

435
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:01,540
 You're vile. 

436
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:05,905
 Ms. Xiang, put the knife down. 

437
00:28:05,905 --> 00:28:07,900
 No, no. Stay calm. Come on. 

438
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:10,000
 Your condition is treatable. 

439
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:12,440
 No, it's not. Not after all this time. 

440
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:13,740
 Even if it were treatable, it's too late now. 

441
00:28:13,740 --> 00:28:15,800
 It is treatable. I'll find you another doctor. 

442
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:17,020
 I'll make sure you're cured. 

443
00:28:17,020 --> 00:28:19,080
 Put the knife down. 

444
00:28:20,780 --> 00:28:23,420
 This isn't contagious. Stop this! 

445
00:28:23,420 --> 00:28:24,700
 Just go home. 

446
00:28:24,700 --> 00:28:27,460
 It's incurable. Incurable. 

447
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:35,180
 - What are you doing? 
 - What are you doing? 

448
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:37,280
 Don't move! 

449
00:28:40,420 --> 00:28:41,940
 Let me go! 

450
00:28:41,940 --> 00:28:43,920
 Let go of me! 

451
00:28:47,420 --> 00:28:50,900
 It was urgent. I rushed him to get his wounds treated. 

452
00:28:50,900 --> 00:28:54,880
The doctor told me a large patch of skin on his back was missing.

453
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:58,040
But he'd only been slashed once.

454
00:28:58,660 --> 00:29:02,140
So, you never saw her again after that?

455
00:29:02,140 --> 00:29:05,180
A long time later, I thought I spotted someone who looked like Xiang Si Lan

456
00:29:05,180 --> 00:29:07,980
near the Flying Horse Statue.

457
00:29:07,980 --> 00:29:10,860
But it couldn't have been her. Her skin was flawless.

458
00:29:10,860 --> 00:29:13,300
The Flying Horse Statue.

459
00:29:13,300 --> 00:29:15,680
The Flying Horse Statue.

460
00:29:36,180 --> 00:29:39,440
We're using a thermal imager to detect life signs.

461
00:29:45,289 --> 00:29:46,891
- What's wrong? 
 - Head!

462
00:29:46,891 --> 00:29:47,947
- What? 
 - Head! The head!

463
00:29:47,947 --> 00:29:49,072
- Head? 
 - Yes.

464
00:29:49,072 --> 00:29:54,260
The wind just flattened the grass. And I saw a huge head flash by.

465
00:29:54,820 --> 00:29:57,300
- Are you hallucinating, Brother Cao. 
 - No way.

466
00:29:57,300 --> 00:29:59,100
- See it? 
 - A mass.

467
00:29:59,100 --> 00:30:00,380
A head flashed by?

468
00:30:00,380 --> 00:30:01,900
- That's ridiculous. 
 - No way.

469
00:30:01,900 --> 00:30:03,700
You think we're filming a TV drama?

470
00:30:03,700 --> 00:30:06,460
Even if we were, you'd be in charge of comedy.

471
00:30:06,460 --> 00:30:10,020
Horror isn't your department.

472
00:30:11,740 --> 00:30:13,720
Was I just imagining things?

473
00:30:15,820 --> 00:30:17,020
Look.

474
00:30:17,020 --> 00:30:19,780
It's Wu Yu Ping.

475
00:30:19,780 --> 00:30:23,340
Never thought she had a rebellious youth.

476
00:30:23,340 --> 00:30:27,940
Such an honest person actually checked in at the Flying Horse Statue. 
    

477
00:30:27,940 --> 00:30:29,620
Look for the check-in records of Song Tie, Ma Chao,

478
00:30:29,620 --> 00:30:32,060
and those who accused Thirteen-Thousand.

479
00:30:32,918 --> 00:30:35,680
- Right. 
 - Ma Chao's here!

480
00:30:37,260 --> 00:30:39,160
Song Tie!

481
00:30:39,160 --> 00:30:41,120
This one. Liu Yi Le.

482
00:30:41,120 --> 00:30:42,478
I remember clearly, like "Happy Children's Day." 
    

483
00:30:42,478 --> 00:30:44,660
He was one of my accusers.

484
00:30:44,660 --> 00:30:45,700
I get it now.

485
00:30:45,700 --> 00:30:49,100
Everyone who came to the Flying Horse Statue was touched by the wind.

486
00:30:49,100 --> 00:30:51,420
That wind is the key.

487
00:30:51,420 --> 00:30:53,380
Wind?

488
00:30:53,380 --> 00:30:57,400
The illusion caused by the relic of ill omen also started with a strange gust.

489
00:30:58,380 --> 00:31:01,480
This wind must be some kind of marker.

490
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:04,140
People thought they were checking in at the Flying Horse Statue.

491
00:31:04,140 --> 00:31:06,020
Instead, they got checked

492
00:31:06,020 --> 00:31:08,240
and tagged with the fragment of the relic of ill omen.

493
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:10,660
Fragment of the relic of ill omen?

494
00:31:14,700 --> 00:31:16,540
I've got a plan...

495
00:31:16,980 --> 00:31:19,160
to lure it out.

496
00:31:32,480 --> 00:31:35,720
Well, from where I'm standing,

497
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:37,340
the Flying Horse Statue looks just like a grand altar.

498
00:31:37,340 --> 00:31:40,200
Chubby's kneeling there like he's paying homage.

499
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:42,560
Quite ceremonial.

500
00:31:42,560 --> 00:31:45,100
What kind of plan is this?

501
00:31:45,100 --> 00:31:47,320
Just throwing me to the wolves, huh?

502
00:31:59,360 --> 00:32:00,800
Here it comes.

503
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:05,440
The head looks bizarre.

504
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:06,880
It's orange.

505
00:32:06,880 --> 00:32:09,080
The rest is pitch black.

506
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:12,160
The chest is like a swirling vortex.

507
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:14,100
Utter darkness.

508
00:32:17,820 --> 00:32:20,140
Cao Yan Hua, get down!

509
00:32:20,140 --> 00:32:21,680
After it!

510
00:32:23,780 --> 00:32:24,920
Are you okay?

511
00:32:24,920 --> 00:32:26,360
Master.

512
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:29,360
I'm not okay. Don't leave!

513
00:32:33,660 --> 00:32:36,420
Mu Dai! Stop chasing.

514
00:32:36,420 --> 00:32:37,980
It's gone.

515
00:32:37,980 --> 00:32:39,500
The imager has a limited range.

516
00:32:39,500 --> 00:32:42,560
Don't worry. She might come back.

517
00:32:45,620 --> 00:32:47,200
Let's go.

518
00:33:01,640 --> 00:33:02,660
- Oh, no. 
 - Brother Cao.

519
00:33:02,660 --> 00:33:04,106
- Oh, my gosh. 
 - What's wrong?

520
00:33:04,106 --> 00:33:05,419
- I was hit by the wind. 
 - A stroke?

521
00:33:05,419 --> 00:33:08,720
That was no ordinary wind.

522
00:33:08,720 --> 00:33:12,361
My skull is ice-cold, and my spine's gone numb.

523
00:33:12,361 --> 00:33:14,560
Hong Sha, you're on watch.

524
00:33:14,560 --> 00:33:15,960
Got it.

525
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:21,480
Master, I feel awful.

526
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:24,740
If I'm right, the fragment of the relic of ill omen is a misnomer.

527
00:33:24,740 --> 00:33:27,020
Xiang Si Lan influences people through that cold wind.

528
00:33:27,020 --> 00:33:31,460
To put it simply, it's like infecting someone with a virus.

529
00:33:31,460 --> 00:33:32,500
A virus?

530
00:33:32,500 --> 00:33:33,880
Normally, there's no sign.

531
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:36,520
But once activated, it takes effect immediately.

532
00:33:36,520 --> 00:33:38,100
Virus of the relic of ill omen?

533
00:33:38,100 --> 00:33:39,140
Virus of the relic of ill omen?

534
00:33:39,140 --> 00:33:41,200
T-Then we're fine.

535
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:42,920
We're immune.

536
00:33:42,920 --> 00:33:44,100
Exactly. We've got an edge.

537
00:33:44,100 --> 00:33:45,740
Right. So why are you suffering?

538
00:33:45,740 --> 00:33:48,700
Do you still feel that chill in your skull and numbness in your limbs?

539
00:33:48,700 --> 00:33:50,480
I'm feeling much better.

540
00:33:50,480 --> 00:33:53,340
- Go on. 
 - What virus did you just mention?

541
00:33:53,340 --> 00:33:55,580
What's its effect?

542
00:33:55,580 --> 00:33:57,780
An enhanced version of rumor-spreading.

543
00:33:57,780 --> 00:34:00,980
It makes the rumor-mongers truly believe their own lies

544
00:34:00,980 --> 00:34:04,600
as if they'd personally witnessed or experienced it.

